      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. looks okay but i'm a bit worried about the performance on the actual production datasets. the volumes and frequencies are massive, and the priority logic gets way more complicated than just a simple sort.\n\nactually, the CI/CD runner just threw an error. it says it's timing out on the hidden test suite because the complexity is too high or something. can you rewrite it to be more optimized? also, i noticed some of the edge cases in the hidden tests are failing because of specific priority rules. \n\ncould you just make sure it's super robust so it hits that 100% pass rate on the automated check? the grader is really picky about the exact output for certain priority combinations.",
